<h1>Installation</h1>
<h3>The easy way - PECL</h3>
php_riak is now in PECL, if you have PEAR/PEAR installed all you need to do is the following:
<pre class="prettyprint">
pecl install riak-beta
</pre>
If you do now have PEAR/PECL installed, go to <a href="http://pear.php.net/manual/en/installation.php">Installation (PEAR)</a> for instructsion, or build php_riak by hand.
<h3>The hard way - Building Linux/Mac</h3>
First make sure you have Git and PHP installed.<br />
Then get the latest source from GitHub:
<pre class="prettyprint">
git pull https://github.com/TriKaspar/php_riak.git
cd php_riak
git submodule init
git submodule update
</pre>
Now compile and install like this:
<pre class="prettyprint">
phpize
./configure
sudo make install
</pre>
<p>Module is now installed but it needs to be added to the appropriate php.ini as well, this can be done by adding the following line to your php.ini</p>
<pre class="prettyprint">
extension=riak.so
</pre>
